('tj', 'Spatial/Geometric', 'A cube painted red on all outer faces is cut into 343 unit cubes (7×7×7). How many unit cubes have exactly two faces painted red?', '["8", "60", "125", "150"]'::jsonb, 1, 'Edge cubes (excluding corners) have exactly 2 painted faces: 12 edges × (n−2) = 12 × 5 = 60 for n=7. ✓'),
('tj', 'Logic/Reasoning', 'In a circuit, a light bulb is wired in series with two switches S1 and S2, so both must be closed to complete the loop. Which switch settings make the light glow?', '["Close S2 only", "Close S1 only", "Any single switch closed", "Close both S1 and S2"]'::jsonb, 3, 'In a series circuit, the current has only one path, so both S1 and S2 must be closed for the bulb to glow — a single closed switch isn''t enough. ✓'),
