('tj', 'Math/Quant', 'A 360-gallon tank starts empty. Valve 1 fills it at 30 gallons/minute. After 2 minutes, Valve 2 (a drain) opens and removes 5 gallons/minute while Valve 1 stays open. How many minutes after the tank starts filling does it become full?', '["13 minutes", "16 minutes", "14 minutes", "12 minutes"]'::jsonb, 2, 'In the first 2 min, 60 gallons fill up, leaving 300 gallons. Once Valve 2 opens, net rate = 30−5 = 25 gal/min, so the remaining 300 gallons take 12 more minutes. Total = 2 + 12 = 14 minutes. ✓'),
('tj', 'Math/Quant', 'Sam drove to a friend''s house at 70 mph and returned along the same route at 40 mph. What was the average speed for the round trip?', '["55 mph", "70 mph", "40 mph", "50.9 mph"]'::jsonb, 3, 'For equal distances at two speeds, average speed is the harmonic mean: 2(70)(40)/(70+40) = 50.9 mph. ✓'),
