('tj', 'Logic/Reasoning', 'Aisha worries about being selected for the championship. Ben tells Aisha, "You''re one of the most skilled people at playing the violin, and everyone who is skilled gets a spot, so you''ll certainly get a spot." Assuming Ben''s premise about Aisha''s talent is true, is the conclusion true?', '["Cannot be true", "Cannot be false", "Probably false, but may be true", "Probably true, but may be false"]'::jsonb, 1, 'If ''everyone skilled gets a spot'' (universal) and Aisha is skilled, then logically Aisha must get a spot — this is a valid syllogism, so the conclusion cannot be false. ✓'),
('tj', 'Math/Quant', 'On a map, Atlanta to Dallas is 6 cm and the actual distance is 250 miles. Using the same scale, what map distance is closest to the actual 700 miles between Atlanta and Baltimore?', '["16 cm", "17 cm", "18 cm", "19 cm"]'::jsonb, 1, 'Scale: 6 cm / 250 mi. Map distance = 6 × (700/250) ≈ 16.8 cm, closest to 17 cm. ✓'),
('tj', 'Math/Quant', 'Cedar Falls''s population increases 12% every 5 years. What is the approximate net percentage change in population after 10 years?', '["25%", "20%", "24%", "29%"]'::jsonb, 0, '10 years is 2 periods of 5 years: growth factor = 1.12^2 ≈ 1.254, a 25% increase. ✓'),
('tj', 'Math/Quant', 'On a map, Miami to Orlando is 6 cm and the actual distance is 400 miles. Using the same scale, what map distance is closest to the actual 1100 miles between Miami and San Francisco?', '["15 cm", "16 cm", "17 cm", "18 cm"]'::jsonb, 1, 'Scale: 6 cm / 400 mi. Map distance = 6 × (1100/400) ≈ 16.5 cm, closest to 16 cm. ✓'),
