('tj', 'Spatial/Geometric', 'A cube assembled from 512 unit cubes (8×8×8) is cut at a 45° angle starting from one of its edges. How many unit cubes are cut in the process?', '["8", "64", "49", "72"]'::jsonb, 1, 'For an n×n×n cube (n=8), a 45° diagonal plane cut starting along one edge slices through n² = 64 unit cubes. ✓'),
('tj', 'Logic/Reasoning', 'Vera worries about being selected for the championship. Derek tells Vera, "You''re one of the most skilled people at gymnastics, and everyone who is skilled gets a spot, so you''ll certainly get a spot." Assuming Derek''s premise about Vera''s talent is true, is the conclusion true?', '["Probably false, but may be true", "Probably true, but may be false", "Cannot be false", "Cannot be true"]'::jsonb, 2, 'If ''everyone skilled gets a spot'' (universal) and Vera is skilled, then logically Vera must get a spot — this is a valid syllogism, so the conclusion cannot be false. ✓'),
